

- Columns:

call_id (sequential integer starting at 1)
agent_id (integer between 1 and 50)
call_duration (integer, seconds, average around 600, min 60)
hold_time (integer, seconds, average around 120, min 0)
csat_score (integer from 1 to 5)
first_call_res (binary: 1 or 0)
repeat_call (binary: 1 or 0)
issue_type (categorical: Billing, Tech, General)
channel (categorical: Voice, Chat, Email)

Data logic:

- Tech issues should have longer average call_duration
- If first_call_res = 0, then repeat_call should be more likely (around 70%)
- If repeat_call = 1, csat_score should decrease
- If hold_time > 180, csat_score should decrease
- If call_duration > 900, csat_score should decrease
- Billing issues should have higher first_call_res rate (~80%)
- Tech issues should have lower first_call_res rate (~60%)



